# Refactor Smell Check
Whenever you refactor, clean up, or reorganize any code in this project, run the `/smell-check` skill on the changed files before calling it done.

I added this because I kept refactoring stuff and then forgetting to check if I introduced new issues. Now it's automatic.

## What counts as a refactor
- Moving or renaming things
- Splitting or merging components
- Rewriting a function or hook
- Cleaning up imports or restructuring a file
- Anything where the behavior stays the same but the code changes

## What to do
1. Make the refactor changes
2. Run `/smell-check` on the files you touched
3. If it finds something, fix it or at least mention it — don't just ignore it
4. Then say you're done
Small style fixes (like fixing a typo or changing a classname) don't need this, that would be annoying.
